# Azure DevOps API — Critical Patterns

## The Descriptor Problem (Most Common Bug)
Azure DevOps has TWO identity systems that do NOT share descriptors:
- Graph API uses `subjectDescriptor` (e.g., `aad.xxx`, `vssgp.xxx`)
- Security ACL API uses old identity `descriptor` (e.g., `Microsoft.TeamFoundation.Identity;S-1-9-...`)

**You MUST resolve between them before correlating users/groups to ACL entries.**
Use: `POST https://vssps.dev.azure.com/{org}/_apis/identities`
with body `{ descriptors: ["vssgp.xxx"] }` → returns objects with both descriptor formats.
Build a bidirectional map at graph-build time. Never assume they match.

## ACL Token Formats
- Project-level git:  `repoV2/{projectId}`
- Repository-level:   `repoV2/{projectId}/{repoId}`
- Fetch with `recurse=true` to get all repo tokens under a project in one call

## Bitmask Permission Logic
- Allow: `(ace.allow & bit) === bit`
- Effective: `effectiveAllow = ace.allow & ~ace.deny`
- Inherited permissions come from `ace.extendedInfo.effectiveAllow` (requires `includeExtendedInfo=true`)
- Over-privileged check: bits 1 (Administer), 8192 (ManagePermissions), 32768 (PullRequestBypassPolicy)

## Pagination — Never Skip
- Graph API truncates at 100 without pagination
- Response header: `x-ms-continuationtoken`
- Query param for next page: `continuationToken={value}`
- Loop until header is absent from response

## Three Base Domains
- Main API:         `https://dev.azure.com/{org}`
- Graph/Identity:   `https://vssps.dev.azure.com/{org}`
- Entitlements:     `https://vsaex.dev.azure.com/{org}`
Getting these wrong returns 404 silently.

## API Versions
- Standard:    `?api-version=7.1`
- Graph:       `?api-version=7.1-preview.1` (also needs Accept header with version)
- Entitlement: `?api-version=7.1-preview.2`

## Group Nesting
- Groups nest up to 10+ levels deep in large orgs
- Always use BFS with a `visited` Set to resolve transitive memberships
- Cap traversal at depth 10 to prevent infinite loops in circular configs

## Rate Limits
- ~200 requests per 5-second window per PAT token
- On 429: read `Retry-After` header, wait, retry — do NOT immediately fail
- For large orgs: batch identity resolution in groups of 50 max